div.p:
1. Both of them are wrought at one moment of time;
                  Secondly the Cautions.
                and in time are neither first nor last: but in order of nature, Faith, as the cause, is first, and then Repentance.

Answ. Sanctification by the bloud of Christ, is either externall, or internall: the former is onely in outward profession of Faith and participation of Word
and Sacraments; and so these Apostates were sanctified;
• d est, seuered from the Iewes and Pagans in profession. But they were neuer inwardly sanctified, nor the bloud of Christ neuer purified their hearts.
